    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AIR CONDITIONING BASIC THEORY, SYSTEM DIAGNOSIS AND SERVICE
        (WITH R-12 REFRIGERANT SYSTEM) - DIAGNOSIS AND TESTING - SYSTEM PRESSURE TEST
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601204" svcproctype="test" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SYSTEM PRESSURE TEST</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Procedure</title>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Run engine at 1800 RPM - hold at speed for 10 min. and during tests.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Set A/C temperature lever on COLD</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Set blower switch on HI</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Open cab windows or doors</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If the vehicle has radiator shutters, open them. If the truck has a fan drive, engage it.
                        These are operated by disconnecting or jumpering the solenoid valve, depending on the system.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Take the readings indicated on the chart.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
